      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "CFD hemolysis index comparison against in-vitro measurements",
      "description": "Relative hemolysis index predicted by the CFD model compared against in-vitro measurements across 5 flow-speed operating points. RH values ranged from 0.71 to 0.94, all satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Mesh independence confirmed at 4.2 million elements.",
      "validationMethod": "Quantitative comparison of normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) between CFD predictions and experimental measurements from FDA benchmark dataset."
